    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1937-09-24T17:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1937-09-24T17:00:00-05:00" n="429"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d429">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">860C.4016/507: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Ambassador in Poland</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Biddle</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1937-09-24T18:00:00-04:00"
                            >September 24, 1937—6 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>69. Department informed by Dr. Stephen Wise<note n="53" xml:id="d429fn53">By
                        telegram of September 23, not printed.</note> that during past 4 days
                    physical violence unrestrained by adequate police measures has been directed
                    against Jews and Jewish business in Warsaw.</p>
                <p>For assistance in reply to Dr. Wise Department requests immediate brief
                    telegraphic report on situation.<note n="54" xml:id="d429fn54">A reply, not
                        printed, was sent to Dr. Wise on October 1, following receipt of telegram
                        No. 114, September 25, from the Ambassador, <hi rend="italic"
                        >infra</hi>.</note>
                </p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Hull</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
